             (Police-serjeant F 10). I received information, went to a house, and found no one at home; I went again about nine o'clock in the evening, and found Coleman in bed, and another boy in another house - I took them to the watch-house; Coleman then said it was not him that took the necklace, it was a boy who lived opposite; and then Kennedy told me where Roark lived, who he said had got the necklace.</p>
